Class ChromatogramWarp

java.lang.Object

      maltcms.commands.fragments.warp.ChromatogramWarp
All Implemented Interfaces:
IFragmentCommand, ICommand<TupleND<IFileFragment>,TupleND<IFileFragment>>, IWorkflowElement, IEventSource<IWorkflowResult>, IConfigurable, IXMLSerializable
Deprecated. 

@Deprecated
public class ChromatogramWarp
extends AFragmentCommand

Use Objects of this class to apply an alignment, warping a source chromatogram to the time/scans of reference chromatogram. Use ChromatogramWarp2 instead!

Author:
Nils.Hoffmann@cebitec.uni-bielefeld.de

warp

public IFileFragment warp(IFileFragment ref,
                          IFileFragment originalFile,
                          IFileFragment processedFile,
                          java.util.List<Tuple2DI> path,
                          boolean toLHS,
                          IWorkflow iw)
Deprecated. 
Warps by projecting data from originalFile to ref, given the alignment path. toLHS determines, whether the alignment reference ref is on the left hand side of the alignment path, or on the right hand side. processedFile is used to keep a backpointer to processing, like anchor finding. The returned FileFragment will have processedFile as its source file, not originalFile, since we want to keep additional information, which we already found out.

Parameters:
ref -
originalFile -
processedFile -
path -
toLHS -
Returns:

warp1D

public IFileFragment warp1D(IFileFragment warpedB,
                            IFileFragment ref,
                            IFileFragment toBeWarped,
                            java.util.List<Tuple2DI> path,
                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> plainVars,
                            boolean toLHS)
Deprecated. 
Warp non-indexed arrays, which are for example scan_acquisisition_time, tic etc.

Parameters:
warpedB - target IFileFragment to store warped arrays
ref - reference IFileFragment
toBeWarped - the to-be-warped IFileFragment
path - alignment path of alignment between a and b
plainVars - list of variable names, which should be warped
toLHS - warp to left hand side
Returns:
FileFragment containing warped data

warp2D

public IFileFragment warp2D(IFileFragment warpedB,
                            IFileFragment ref,
                            IFileFragment toBeWarped,
                            java.util.List<Tuple2DI> path,
                            java.util.List<java.lang.String> indexedVars,
                            boolean toLHS)
Deprecated. 
Warp indexed arrays, which are lists of 1D arrays, so pseudo 2D. In this case limited to mass_values and intensity_values.

Parameters:
warpedB - target IFileFragment to store warped arrays
ref - reference IFileFragment
toBeWarped - the to-be-warped IFileFragment
path - alignment path of alignment between a and b
plainVars - list of variable names, which should be warped
toLHS - whether warping should be done from right to left (true) or vice versa (false)
Returns:
FileFragment containing warped data

warpAnchors

public void warpAnchors(IFileFragment warped,
                        IFileFragment toBeWarped,
                        java.util.List<Tuple2DI> path,
                        boolean toLHS)
Deprecated. 
Warp anchors according to pairwise scan mapping in path, reads anchors from processedFile and stores them in warped file. If toLHS is true, assumes target scale of warp on left side of path, processedFile should contain the data to the right side of the path.

Parameters:
warped -
processedFile -
path -
toLHS -
